We have a drive train set up with 3 Falcon500s into on Gearbox they are set up with one master and two slaves.

We can run this in either open or closed loop. Both configClosedloopRamp and configOpenloopRamp are set to ZERO

When inputting a from a 0 to 1 in percent output the motors still seems to ramp.

What other configurations could be effecting the responce and what other info would you like to know. I’m a bit puzzled and know this shutoff be obvious.

Trends in Phoenix tuner also show the output as ramping

A bit of Testing and observation. We started to add the configuration loops to our isolated code and found the first one that repeated the results:

leftTalonMaster.configStatorCurrentLimit(new StatorCurrentLimitConfiguration(true, 10, 25, 1.0));
//leftTalonMaster.configSupplyCurrentLimit(new SupplyCurrentLimitConfiguration(true, 5, 15, 0.5);

It seems configStatorCurrentLimit effects the ramp rate. We thought we were protecting the Motors and system for stalls

That’s a 10-amp limit triggered at 25 amps, which will get hit regularly on pretty much any mechanism. Explains your “sinusoid” in the traces as power comes on, hits 25, gets throttled to 10…

Mechanically it’ll just look like a ramp rate, it cuts on and off too quickly to see a physical stutter on the robot.
